elem_dict.key: 1299_786_351_63_Chickens are showing up in many suburban backyards. They’re relatively easy to raise and don’t take up a lot of space. Having a source of farm-fresh eggs right outside your door may tempt you to give chicken keeping a try. Before you rush out and buy a coop, it’s important to consider a few details. This guide will teach you the basics of how to raise chickens and which  chicken supplies  you need to keep them healthy and happy. We’ll also answer common questions, such as: “How much do chickens cost?” and “At what age do chickens start laying eggs?”
